<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL, In-Chassis
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL, In-Chassis</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the rear oil seal removed, the wear sleeve can be removed using a muffler chisel and
                air hammer (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050716">7.16</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE CAREFUL NOT TO NICK THE CRANKSHAFT FLANGE DURING THIS PROCEDURE. USE THIS METHOD ONLY WHEN
                        THE REPAIR IS TO BE DONE IN-CHASSIS WITH THE FLYWHEEL HOUSING AND REAR OIL SEAL CARRIER IN
                        PLACE.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard wear sleeve.</para>
            <figure id="ef1050715" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3067" filename="../figeg3/EG3067.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.15.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Pry Bar</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Rear Oil Seal</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Screw (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050716" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3055" filename="../figeg3/EG3055.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.16.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Muffler Chisel</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Seal Carrier</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Rear Oil Seal</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
